<body>
    <div class="container-fluid">
        <h1 class="lead">EMDR Cycle</h1>
        <div id="my-wizard" class="wizard">
        <!-- Setting up steps row -->
            <ul class="steps">
                <li data-target="#step1" class="active"><span class="badge badge-info">1</span>Assessment<span class="chevron"></span></li>
                <li data-target="#step2"><span class="badge">2</span>Overview<span class="chevron"></span></li>
                <li data-target="#step3"><span class="badge">3</span>Desensitization<span class="chevron"></span></li>
                <li data-target="#step4"><span class="badge">4</span>Installation<span class="chevron"></span></li>
                <li data-target="#step5"><span class="badge">5</span>Body Scan<span class="chevron"></span></li>
                <li data-target="#step6"><span class="badge">6</span>Closure<span class="chevron"></span></li>
            </ul>
            <div class="actions">
                <button class="btn btn-mini btn-prev"> <i class="icon-arrow-left"></i>Prev</button>
                <button class="btn btn-mini btn-next" data-last="Finish">Next<i class="icon-arrow-right"></i></button>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-pane active alert alert-info" id="step1">
                <div id="assessment_form"><%= render 'form' %></div>
            </div>

            <div class="step-pane alert alert-info" id="step2">
               <h3 class="lead">Instructions for Bilateral Stimulation via Virtual Reality</h3>
               <p style="font-size:16px"><em>Virtual reality exposure may cause mismatches between physical and motion cues. This could potentially lead to nausea known as "simulation sickness". If patient experiences "simulation sickness", pause briefly and recenter patient. If problems persist, find alternatives for bilateral stimulation.</em></p>
               <h4>Desensitization Phase</h4>
               <p>Instruct patient to hold in focus a picture of traumatic event, a negative self perception, and/or body sensation associated with event.<p>
                <p>Select and turn on proper virtual stimulation environment on mobile device and mount device within Google Cardboard VR headset.</p>
                <p>Have the patient recall the traumatic event for a short period (30-45s) while simultaneously undergoing bilateral stimulation by holding headset to eyes. The VR stimulus for EMDR consists of rapid hand movements in the patient's field of vision. Following each set, briefly check in with patient, provide cognitive interweaves, and assess patient's level of distress on a scale 0-10.</p>
                <p>Continue until patient's target event feels neutral 0.</p>
               <h4>Installation Phase</h4>
               <p>Instruct patient to revisit positive cognition/affirmation, while undergoing short (30-45s) sets of VR bilateral stimulation.</p>
               <p>Following each set, briefly check in with patient and assess patient's validation of cognition on a scale of 1-7.</p>
               <p>Continue until patient's validation of cognition for positive affirmation is totally valid (7).</p>
               <h4>Body Scan</h4>
               <p>Scan patient body for sensations / tensions, continue with BLS if any lingering sensations.</p>
            </div>
    
            <div class="step-pane" id="step3">
                <div class="row-fluid"> 
                    <div class="span6 alert alert-info">
                        <%= render 'dataform' %>
                    </div>
                    <div class="span6" id="bls_phase4">
                        <br>
                        <p>BLS Desensitization Chart</p>
                        <br>
                        <%= render 'chart' %>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="step-pane" id="step4">
                <div class="row-fluid">
                    <div class="span6 alert alert-info">
                        <%= render 'graphform' %>
                    </div>
                    <div class="span6" id="bls_install4">
                        <br>
                        <p>BLS Installation Chart</p>
                        <br>
                        <%= render 'graph' %>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="step-pane alert alert-info" id="step5">
                <h4>Closure</h4>
                <br>
                <% if Cycle.count.zero? %>
                   <p>A Cycle has not been logged.</p>
                <% else %>
                    <%= render 'closeform' %>
                <% end %>
            </div>

            <div class="step-pane alert alert-info" id="step6">
                <h4>Closure</h4>
                <p>Closure is different if session is complete or incomplete. If incomplete, instruct patient to imagine safe place to hold any distress and guide patient to neutral or positive state prior to leaving session.</p>
                <p>Beginning of next session, review patients progress over the week and discuss any new sensation/experiences that need to be addressed.</p>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>
 
</body>